I think I've found it. In JSVGCanvas.java from line 1140 the tooltip is 
fetched from the hashmap, however it searches on the wrong node. I think the 
code should be:

            if (toolTipMap != null && lastTarget != null) {
        		Node node = ((Element)lastTarget).getParentNode();
        		if (node!=null) {
	                Object o = toolTipMap.get(node);
	                final String theToolTip;
	                if (o == null) theToolTip = null;
	                else           theToolTip = (String)o;
	                if (prevLastTarget != lastTarget)
	                    EventQueue.invokeLater(new ToolTipRunnable
(theToolTip));
        		}
            }

Am I right??
